OL,6,FInvestigators twice sent files for a
OL,7,Fcharging decision to the Crown
OL,8,FProsecution Service ` once in 2008
OL,9,Frelating to three victims and again in
OL,10,F2015 linked to one other.
OL,12,FOn another three occasions ` in 2018,
OL,13,F2021 and 2023 ` the CPS was asked for
OL,14,Fwhat is called early investigative
OL,15,Fadvice, but the matters were not
OL,16,Fpursued further by police.
OL,18,FThe Faldgate law firm, which
OL,19,Frepresents the Al Fayed estate, has
OL,20,Fbeen contacted for comment.
